%N A395713 Number of binary relations on an n-set that are neither reflexive nor symmetric nor transitive.
%C A395713 By inclusion-exclusion on the three properties R, S, T: a(n) = 2^(n^2) - |R| - |S| - |T| + |R and S| + |R and T| + |S and T| - |R and S and T|. Here, R, S, T are respectively the sets of relations that reflexive, symmetric and transitive respectively.
%F A395713 a(n) = 2^(n^2) - 2^(n^2-n) - 2^(n*(n+1)/2) - A006905(n) + 2^(n*(n-1)/2) + A000798(n) + A000110(n+1) - A000110(n).
%e A395713 For n=3 there are 2^9 = 512 binary relations on {1,2,3}. Of these, 64 are reflexive, 64 are symmetric, and 171 are transitive; applying inclusion-exclusion, 252 are reflexive or symmetric or transitive, leaving a(3) = 512 - 252 = 260.
%Y A395713 Cf. A002416, A053763, A006905, A000798, A000110.
